===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|や|yomi=k|alt=家}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*ya|id=house}}.

The semantics appear to have been extended as follows: "house, place of residence" (as in {{ja-r|宮|みや|[[shrine]], the place where a god resides}}) > "place (of human occupation or use)" (as in {{ja-r|小屋|こや|hut, shed}}) > "shop, establishment (of a particular trade/business)" (as in {{ja-r|パン屋|パンや|bakery}}) > "-er (someone of a particular trade/business)" (as in {{ja-r|パン屋|パンや|baker}}) > "-er (someone with a particular characteristic)" (as in {{ja-r|寂しがり屋|さびしがりや|one susceptible to loneliness}}. The semantic transferral between an establishment and the professional associated with it may be seen (though in opposite order) in the use of English ''doctor'' in reference to the doctor's ''office'' (as in phrases like "going to the doctor").

